ZCZC GE59
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 232300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A RIDGE FM A HIGH PRESSURE LOCATED TO THE N OF THE UK
EXTENDS ACROSS UK WATERS AND THE N SEA BRINGING A GENERALLY NE AIRFLOW ACROSS
THE COUNTRY. AT THE SAME TIME AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE LIES JUST W OF THE
IBERIAN PENINSULA MOV SLWY NE. THROUGH TUESDAY THE CENTRE OF THE HIGH MIGRATES
S TO LIE SHETLAND BY MIDNIGHT WITH THE IBERIAN LOW JUST NW OF SPAIN PUSHING
FRONTS TOWARDS SW UK. THE HIGH CONTINUES TO MOV S ON WEDNESDAY TO BE CENTRED
JUST E OF SCOTLAND WITH TEH SW LOW FLN. THIS RESULTING IN LIGHT WINDS AND
SETTLED CONDITIONS. ON THURSDAY THE HIGH STAYS SLOW MOV WITH FRONTS FM AN
ATLANTIC LOW APPOACHING THE FAR SW OF THE COUNTRY. NO STRG WINDS OR GALES
ARE EXP TO AFFECT THE CULLERCOATS REGION THROUGHOUT THE FCST PERIOD
